label: Village study arm
definition: Abbreviation refers to randomization group. Villages were randomized into one of three arms and given different treatment regimens. Refer to study page for more detail.

label: Grade in school at enrollment
codebookDescription: Grade in school when child was enrolled

label: Schistosoma haematobium (per 10 ml), by microscopy
definition: Number of Schistosoma haematobium eggs calculated per 10 ml urine
codebookDescription: Number of  schistosoma haematobium eggs in 10 ml from one filter/slide from a urine sample

label: Schistosoma haematobium, by microscopy
definition: Presence or absence of Schistosoma haematobium eggs in study participant,  based on detection the urine sample
codebookDescription: Presence or absence of Schistosoma haematobium eggs in study participant,  based on detection the urine sample
